  <TITLE>Possibility of disabling Redis SSL/TLS certificate validation</TITLE>
  <DESCRIPTION>We'd like to use &quot;Heroku Data for Redis&quot;, which offers Redis connections with and without TLS. However, the server certificate is self-signed and the Heroku documentation states you have to disable certificate verification. This can't be done with the connection string, according to StackOverflow answers it can only be done by changing the StackExchange.Redis connection options after parsing but before connecting. But I can't find a way to do that in Orchard Core. Could it be done, or are we stuck with unencrypted Redis connections?</DESCRIPTION>
